    <p><strong>A commercial vegetable cutting machine in India costs between ₹15,000 for a basic Indian-made vegetable cutter and over ₹8,00,000 for a fully-loaded European continuous-feed vegetable processor.</strong> If you run a restaurant, hotel, catering business, or cloud kitchen, vegetable prep is the single most time-consuming task in your kitchen. Onions, potatoes, carrots, cabbage, beans, tomatoes — every Indian menu demands huge volumes of vegetables cut into precise shapes, day after day. A commercial vegetable cutting machine can reduce your prep time by 70–90%, free up labour, and deliver far more consistent results than hand-chopping ever could.</p>

    <p>This guide covers every category of commercial vegetable processing equipment available in India in 2026: vegetable cutters, onion cutting machines, potato peelers, potato chips slicers, food processors, and vegetable washing machines. We include real market prices, capacity specifications, brand comparisons, and practical guidance on choosing the right machine for your specific operation. Whether you need to dice 50 kg of onions an hour or peel 200 kg of potatoes for a banquet, this guide will help you make the right investment.</p>

