    <h2>3. Commercial Potato Peeler Machine: Abrasive Drum Technology</h2>

    <p>A commercial potato peeler machine is one of the simplest and most satisfying pieces of equipment in a commercial kitchen. You load raw, dirty potatoes into a drum with an abrasive (rough) interior surface, add water, and turn it on. The drum rotates, the abrasive surface scrubs off the skin, and the water washes the peelings out through a drain. Within 2–4 minutes, you have a batch of cleanly peeled potatoes ready for cutting.</p>

    <h3>How Abrasive Drum Potato Peelers Work</h3>

    <p>The abrasive drum potato peeler uses a carborundum (silicon carbide) coated turntable and interior walls. As the turntable rotates, potatoes tumble and rub against the abrasive surface, which removes the skin. A continuous water supply washes the peelings away through a waste outlet. The peeling time depends on the potato variety, age, and skin thickness — new potatoes with thin skins peel faster than older potatoes with thicker skins.</p>

    <p>Key specifications to consider include batch capacity (how many kg per load), peeling time per batch, water consumption, and motor power. Most commercial potato peelers can also peel other root vegetables like carrots, beetroot, and sweet potatoes — though some vegetables peel better than others depending on their skin characteristics.</p>

