    <h2>6. Commercial Vegetable Washing Machines</h2>

    <p>Vegetable washing is often overlooked but critically important, especially for operations that process large volumes or serve raw/minimally-cooked vegetables. Commercial vegetable washing machines use high-pressure water jets, air bubble agitation, or ozone treatment to remove dirt, pesticide residues, and surface bacteria from vegetables efficiently.</p>

    <p><strong>Bubble Wash Machines:</strong> These use air compressors to create vigorous bubbles in a water tank, which gently agitate the vegetables and dislodge dirt and contaminants without bruising delicate produce. Capacity: 50–500 kg/hr. Price: ₹30,000–₹5,00,000. Used in hotels, central kitchens, and food factories.</p>

    <p><strong>Spray Wash Machines:</strong> High-pressure water sprays wash vegetables as they pass through on a conveyor. More suitable for root vegetables and sturdy produce. Capacity: 100–1,000 kg/hr. Price: ₹50,000–₹8,00,000.</p>

    <p><strong>Ozone Vegetable Washers:</strong> These infuse ozone into the wash water, which helps eliminate pesticide residues and bacteria. Popular in health-conscious establishments and organic food processing. Price: ₹40,000–₹3,00,000.</p>

    <p>For most restaurants, a simple rinse-and-soak process is sufficient. But hotels processing hundreds of kilograms of salad vegetables daily, or cloud kitchens that need to guarantee food safety at scale, should seriously consider an automated vegetable washing system. For cloud kitchen setup guidance, see our <a href="/blog/cloud-kitchen-equipment">cloud kitchen equipment guide</a>.</p>

