    <h2>11. Application Guide: Which Machines for Which Business?</h2>

    <h3>Small Restaurant / Cafe (50–100 covers/day)</h3>
    <p>A small restaurant typically needs a basic vegetable cutter and possibly a potato peeler. A combination food processor like the Robot Coupe R301 Ultra (which handles both bowl processing and continuous-feed cutting) is often the smartest single investment. Budget: ₹70,000–₹1,50,000 for all vegetable processing equipment.</p>

    <h3>Mid-Size Restaurant / Hotel Kitchen (100–300 covers/day)</h3>
    <p>This is where dedicated machines start making sense. A continuous-feed vegetable cutter, a potato peeler, and a separate food processor for sauces and pastes. Consider an onion cutter if your menu is onion-heavy. Budget: ₹1,50,000–₹4,00,000.</p>

    <h3>Large Hotel / Banquet Catering (300+ covers/day)</h3>
    <p>Heavy-duty European vegetable cutters, large-capacity potato peelers, industrial food processors, and possibly a vegetable washing machine. Multiple machines running simultaneously during peak prep hours. Budget: ₹4,00,000–₹15,00,000+.</p>

    <h3>Cloud Kitchen / Dark Kitchen</h3>
    <p>Cloud kitchens prioritize space efficiency. Combination machines that handle multiple functions in a small footprint are ideal. A Robot Coupe CL50 or Hallde RG-250 can handle most vegetable cutting needs, and a compact food processor covers sauces and pastes. See our <a href="/blog/cloud-kitchen-equipment">cloud kitchen equipment guide</a> for full recommendations.</p>

    <h3>Chips / Snack Manufacturing Unit</h3>
    <p>Dedicated potato peeler (20–30 kg batch), continuous potato chips slicer (200+ kg/hr), and a starch-removal washing system. Indian-made equipment is often sufficient for this application and represents better value. Budget: ₹1,00,000–₹5,00,000 depending on scale.</p>

    <h3>Central Commissary / Food Factory</h3>
    <p>Industrial-grade vegetable processing lines including heavy-duty cutters, large peelers, washing systems, and possibly automated dicing/slicing lines. This is where brands like Robot Coupe, Hallde, and industrial equipment from manufacturers like Urschel and FAM become relevant. Budget: ₹10,00,000–₹50,00,000+.</p>

    <h2>12. Where to Buy Commercial Vegetable Machines in India</h2>

    <p>Finding the right equipment at the right price requires knowing where to look. Here are your main options:</p>

    <p><strong>Authorized Brand Dealers:</strong> For premium brands like Robot Coupe, Hallde, and Dito Sama, always buy from authorized dealers. This ensures genuine products, valid warranties, and access to spare parts and service. Robot Coupe has dealers in all major Indian cities — Delhi, Mumbai, Bangalore, Chennai, Hyderabad, Kolkata, and Pune. Ask for the dealer's authorization certificate.</p>

    <p><strong>Commercial Kitchen Equipment Markets:</strong> Every major Indian city has dedicated equipment markets. Delhi's Mary Market and Rewari Line (Old Delhi), Mumbai's Lohar Chawl and Mohammed Ali Road, Chennai's Parrys Corner, and Bangalore's SP Road are well-known hubs. These markets are excellent for Indian-made equipment and often offer better prices than online channels.</p>

    <p><strong>Online Marketplaces:</strong> IndiaMART, TradeIndia, and Alibaba (for direct imports) are useful for comparing prices and finding suppliers. However, always inspect equipment in person before finalizing a purchase, especially for machines above ₹50,000. Online prices are often negotiable.</p>

    <p><strong>BakeDesk:</strong> We connect buyers with verified equipment dealers across India. Tell us what you need and we will get you competitive quotes from multiple dealers — saving you the time and effort of visiting markets and negotiating individually.</p>

